Whereas 1 in 4 new HIV infections occurs among young
			 people between the ages of 13 and 24, accounting for 1,000 new cases every
			 month;

Whereas African-American youth bear a disproportionate
			 burden of the epidemic, representing 60 percent of new infections in young
			 people;

Whereas new HIV infections among 13- to 29-year-old
			 African-American men who have sex with men (MSM) increased 48 percent from 2006
			 through 2009;

Whereas the Ryan White Part D Program is one of the
			 national efforts to link HIV positive youth to medical care and support
